The render tree is already being built before `OnInitialized` is called and the `foreach` will be executed at a time where `users` is still `null`. You can either assign `users` and empty array first or, _my_ preferred variant, use an `if` to check if you should try to render the users at all. This is also the way the template project (the one with weather forecasts) does it.

```
@page &quot;/&quot;
@using Models
@using Data
@inject UserService us

&lt;form method=&quot;post&quot;&gt;
    &lt;input asp-page=&quot;/Create&quot; type=&quot;button&quot; value=&quot;Neuen Benutzer erstellen&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;

@if (users == null)
{
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Loading...&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
}
else
{
    &lt;form method=&quot;post&quot;&gt;
        &lt;table class=&quot;table&quot;&gt;
            &lt;thead&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;
                    &lt;th&gt;ID&lt;/th&gt;
                    &lt;th&gt;UserID&lt;/th&gt;
                    &lt;th&gt;Name&lt;/th&gt;
                    &lt;th&gt;Supervisor&lt;/th&gt;
                    &lt;th&gt;Ersteller&lt;/th&gt;
                    &lt;th&gt;Erstelldatum&lt;/th&gt;
                    &lt;th&gt;Optionen&lt;/th&gt;
                &lt;/tr&gt;
            &lt;/thead&gt;
            &lt;tbody&gt;
                @foreach (var user in users)
                {
                    &lt;tr&gt;
                        &lt;td&gt;@user.PkId&lt;/td&gt;
                        &lt;td&gt;@user.UserId&lt;/td&gt;
                        &lt;td&gt;@user.FirstName @user.LastName&lt;/td&gt;
                        &lt;td&gt;@user.Supervisor&lt;/td&gt;
                        &lt;td&gt;@user.CreationUser&lt;/td&gt;
                        &lt;td&gt;@user.CreationDate&lt;/td&gt;
                        &lt;td&gt;
                            &lt;a&gt;Delete Account&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                            &lt;a asp-page=&quot;/Edit&quot;&gt; Edit Account&lt;/a&gt;
                        &lt;/td&gt;
                    &lt;/tr&gt;
                }
            &lt;/tbody&gt;
        &lt;/table&gt;
    &lt;/form&gt;
}

@code 
{
    Users[] users;

    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        users = await us.GetUsersAsync();
    }
}
```

The problem is in the below code line :

     u = await _context.Users.ToArrayAsync();

When you use await in the above code ,  the method `GetUsersAsync` is suspended until the awaited task is complete ，then the method `OnInitializedAsync` will also be suspended .So the Users array is null when a component gets rendered

Change the above code to

     u = _context.Users.ToArray();

